-- Aval, BM&FBovespa, BR Malls Participacoes: Latin America Equity Preview
-- Eduardo Thomson
-- 2010-07-16T04:25:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-16/aval-bm-fbovespa-br-malls-participacoes-latin-america-equity-preview.html

          
          
             The following companies may have
unusual price changes in Latin American trading. Stock symbols
are in parentheses and share prices reflect the previous close.  
 The  MSCI Latin America Index  fell 0.2 percent to 3,863.52.
In Brazil, preferred shares usually are the most-traded class of
stock.  
 Brazil  
 BM&FBovespa SA  (BVMF3 BS): The owner of Latin America’s
biggest bourse was raised to “buy” from “underperform” by Banco
Santander SA analysts Henrique Navarro and  Boris Molina , who
said strong share prices and accelerating turnover amid
technological innovation should boost the company’s revenue.
The shares may rise to 16.90 reais next year, compared with a
2010 forecast of 14 reais, the analysts said. BM&FBovespa rose
2.5 percent to 11.99 reais.  
 BR Malls Participacoes SA  (BRML3 BS): Equity International
sold 18.2 million shares in the Brazilian shopping malls
developer for $245 million. BR Malls rose 5.9 percent to 24.10
reais.  
 Centrais Eletricas Brasileiras SA  (ELET6 BS): Latin
America’s largest utility was rated “hold” in new coverage by
Banco Santander SA analysts Marcio Prado and Maria Carolina
Carneiro, who said they see the need for further measures even
after the company improved its corporate governance policies.
The stock rose 0.8 percent to 26.01 reais.  
 Colombia  
 Grupo Aval Acciones y Valores SA  (AVAL CB): Colombia’s
biggest financial holding company plans to issue $1 billion in
local shares as part of the purchase of BAC-Credomatic GECF Inc,
company executives said. Aval rose 1.9 percent to 980 pesos.  
